article.headline: Duquesne 84, George Washington 59
article.story: PITTSBURGH -- Bill Clark had 23 points, 10 rebounds and four assists as Duquesne cruised past George Washington 84-59 on Wednesday night, the Dukes' 11th consecutive victory. Duquesne (16-5, 8-0 Atlantic 10 Conference) has beaten every opponent during this streak by double digits, and this latest one -- in front of 3,016 fans -- may have been the easiest. The Dukes, who had five players in double figures in scoring, led by 12 at the half and forced 26 turnovers. With the win, combined with Xavier's 66-62 loss at Charlotte, Duquesne is now in sole possession of first place in the Atlantic 10. Tony Taylor scored 21 for the Colonials (11-11, 4-4).
